 and reliably; exploratory data analysis to generate hypotheses and intuition; prediction based on statistical methods such as regression and classification; and communication of results through visualization, stories, and interpretable summaries.</li>\n<li><a href=\"http://cm.dce.harvard.edu/2015/01/14328/publicationListing.shtml\">Lectures</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"http://cs109.github.io/2014/pages/schedule.html\">Slides</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"http://cs109.github.io/2014/pages/homework.html\">Labs and Assignments</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"http://cs109.github.io/2014/\">2014 Lectures</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"http://cm.dce.harvard.edu/2014/01/14328/publicationListing.shtml\">2013 Lectures</a> <em>(slightly better)</em></li>\n</ul>\n</li>","updatedAt":"2016-01-11T07:35:07.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"alebcay/awesome-shell","categoryHTML":"<h2>Multimedia and File Formats</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://github.com/beetbox/beets\">Beets</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/beetbox/beets\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">11.2k</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":11180,\"repo\":\"beetbox/beets\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END--> - Music library manager and MusicBrainz tagger</li>","updatedAt":"2016-01-11T04:27:23.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"moul/awesome-ssh","categoryHTML":"<h2>Apps</h2><h3>Network</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://mosh.mit.edu\">Mosh</a> - The mobile shell.</li>","updatedAt":"2016-01-11T00:06:13.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"moul/awesome-ssh",